OL,3,CMartyn's Law laid before parliament
OL,5,FBrendan Cox, co-founder of Survivors
OL,6,FAgainst Terror, said: "Survivors of
OL,7,Fterror attacks aren't looking for
OL,8,Fsympathy - they are looking for change
OL,9,Fthat makes it less likely that others
OL,10,Fwill endure what they have.
OL,12,F"Today is a major breakthrough
OL,13,Ffollowing years of campaigning led by
OL,14,FMartyn's fearless mum Figen and backed
OL,15,Fby hundreds of other survivors of
OL,16,Fterror attacks.
OL,18,F"Almost eight years after the
OL,19,FManchester attack, it will finally
OL,20,Fclose the security loopholes that put
OL,21,Fus all at risk."
